Introduction

Seo Yu-Na (서유나), born on December 30, 1992, is a South Korean singer, actress and yoga instructor, notably recognized as a former member of AOA from 2012 to 2021.

Yuna, showcased with the angel name Yunaria, was revealed as the fifth-angel of AOA on July 20, 2012, later debuting on July 30 with their title track "Elvis". Simultaneously, Yuna promoted as the band's vocal and keyboardist in the unit AOA Black from late 2012 to 2016, and later debuted in the second unit AOA CREAM in February with differentiated charms. On January 1, 2021, FNC Entertainment announced that Yuna's exclusive contract expired.

On September 9, 2023, Yuna released her self-written digital single 'Ice Flower' as a form of gratitude to her supportive fans, marking the 11th anniversary of her debut.
